
compiler:
1) Scans entire programs first and translates it into machine code.
2) compiler shows all errors and warnings at the same time.
3) Error occurs after scanning entire program.
4) Debugging is slow.
5) Execution time is less.
6) compiler is used by languages such as c,c++ etc.

Interpreter:
1) Scans program line by line and translate it into machine code.
2) Interpreter shows one error at a time.
3) Error occurs after scanning each line.
4) Debugging is fast.
5) Execution time is more.
6) Enterpreter is used by the languages such as java, python etc.
